article.description: — Noah Harris' 15 points helped Marist defeat Bucknell 73-49 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Marist knocks off Bucknell 73-49
article.story: POUGHKEEPSIE, N.Y. -- — Noah Harris' 15 points helped Marist defeat Bucknell 73-49 on Saturday night. Harris was 5-of-8 shooting (5 for 7 from 3-point range) for the Red Foxes (3-2). Jaden Daughtry added 12 points and Jackson Price had nine points and eight rebounds. The Bison (2-6) were led in scoring by Josh Bascoe, who finished with 14 points. Bucknell also got 10 points from Ruot Bijiek. Quin Berger also put up eight points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
